law.text:
The State Retirement and Pension System consists of:
the Correctional Officers' Retirement System, established on July 1, 1974;
the Employees' Pension System, established on January 1, 1980;
the Employees' Retirement System, established on October 1, 1941;
the Judges' Retirement System, which consists of:
the contributory plan, established on July 1, 1969; and
the noncontributory plan, established on April 7, 1904;
the Legislative Pension Plan;
the Local Fire and Police System, established on July 1, 1989;
the Law Enforcement Officers' Pension System, established on July 2, 1990;
the State Police Retirement System, established on July 1, 1949;
the Teachers' Pension System, established on January 1, 1980;
the Teachers' Retirement System, established on August 1, 1927; and
any other system or subsystem that the Board of Trustees administers.
